<a name="newsitem951299252,7301,"></a>
<p><strong><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2" color="#FBB202"><a name="$newstime">GigaPixel Giga3D Architecture</a></font> </strong><small><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="1" color="#000000">Posted Wednesday, February 23 3:47 by <a href="mailto:kornel@linux3d.net">kornel</a></font></small><br> <font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://www.3dgn.com/hardware/">Ryan Brucks at 3dgn </a> published an amazing article on the <a href="http://www.3dgn.com/hardware/articles/giga3d/4.shtml">GigaPixel Architecture.</a> If you don't know, the GigaPixel graphics chipset will be used in Microsoft's upcoming X-Box console so if you wanna know why it was chosen instead of the GeForce 256 chipset, read ahead.</font></p>

