<p><strong><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2" color="#FBB202"><a name="$newstime">3dfx goes Open Source</a></font> </strong><small><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="1" color="#000000">Posted Friday, November 19 3:47 by <a href="mailto:armin@linux3d.net">armin</a></font></small><br> <font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://www.3dfx.com">3dfx</a> released a Voodoo3 X Server with Mesa-based OpenGL API support. Installing it will disable Glide under Linux (!). Quake 3 is supposed to run and so are all OpenGL applications that you can compile from source. Unreal Tournament, Myth 2 and Quake 1/2 will not work with it.<br><br>You can download this driver package <a href="http://www.3dfxgamers.com/view.asp?IOID=1024">here</a>.</font></p>

