<p><strong><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2" color="#FBB202"><a name="$newstime">SMP box progress</a></font> </strong><small><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="1" color="#000000">Posted Tuesday, August 3 12:12 by <a href="mailto:armin@linux3d.net">armin</a></font></small><br> <font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2" color="#000000">Ok, the SMP box is here and running fine at 462 MHz now after it ran through the night at 412, it is a really bad boy at cracking RC5 at about 2.5 MKeys/sec when both CPUs are fully dedicated to it. I will definately need to do something about circulation, though, the CPUs are in a bad position behind the power supply and drive bay cables where they have trouble getting cool outside air. Luckily the case allows for removal of the top so that's what I'm doing for now, with the intent to add two 50 mm fans into that top once I get my hands on suitable power tools and the money for the parts.Thanks go to Shane Jordan for pointing my nose in the right direction on the networking stuff, I got it to talk to the internet through the ISDN dialup machine that way.</font></p>

