<p><strong><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2" color="#FBB202"><a name="$newstime">New beta version of Crystal Space (0.13r012)</a></font> </strong><small><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="1" color="#000000">Posted Saturday, July 3 2:40 by <a href="mailto:kornel@linux3d.net">kornel</a></font></small><br> <font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="2" color="#000000">Jorrit Tyberghein from <a href="http://crystal.linuxgames.com">Crystal Space</a> sent word that he has a new version of Crystal Space available for download. Crystal Space can be found at <a href="http://crystal.linuxgames.com">http://crystal.linuxgames.com</a> and is an Open Source 3D engine for Linux, Windows, OS/2, BeOS, Macintosh, DOS, NextStep, FreeBSD, ... It uses Direct3D, OpenGL, Glide, or software rendering.<br><br>" This is a beta release with version number 0.13r012. We're developing on CVS right now so frequency of beta releases has dropped a bit.<br><br>A lot has changed since 0.13r011. There have been many bugs fixed and lots of improvements with OpenGL and Direct3D renderer. There are also some speed improvements. Check the URL for a complete list. " </font></p>

